## 1. Create a Peer

Start by creating a new Peer instance.

```js
var peer = new ZYNQ.Peer();
```

Each peer is assigned a unique ID automatically when it is ready.

## 2. Get your Peer ID

```js
peer.on('ready', function(id) {
  console.log('My peer ID is: ' + id);
});
```

You will use this ID to connect with other peers.

To connect to another peer, you need their peer ID.

```js
peer.on('ready', (id) => {
  console.log('Share this ID:', id);
});
```

You are responsible for sharing IDs between clients (via server, chat, etc).

## Start a connection

```js
var conn = peer.connect('dest-peer-id');
```

## Receive a connection

```js
peer.on('connection', function(conn) {
  conn.on('open', function() {

    // Receive data
    conn.on('data', function(data) {
      console.log('Received:', data);
    });

    // Send data
    conn.send('Hello!');
  });
});
```

Data connections allow real-time messaging between peers.

## Start a call

```js
var call = peer.call('dest-peer-id', mediaStream);
```

## Answer a call

```js
peer.on('call', function(call) {
  call.answer(mediaStream);
});
```

## Receive remote stream

```js
call.on('stream', function(stream) {
  video.srcObject = stream;
});
```

Media streams are provided via getUserMedia and enable video/audio communication.

```js
const games = new ZYNQ.games();

await games.init();
```

After initialization, the full game list is available in `.list`.

## Search games

```js
games.search('minecraft');
console.log(games.list);
```

## Reset filters

```js
games.reset();
```

## Get random game

```js
const game = games.getRandomOne();
```

## Filter by category

```js
games.getByCategory('action');
```

## Only supported devices

```js
games.filterSupported();
```

## Favorites

```js
games.toggleFavorite('game-alias');
games.filterFavorites();
```
